article.headline: IUPUI 67, Southern Utah 66
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS, Ind.(AP) -- Brandon Cameron made two free throws with 10 seconds remaining to lift IUPUI over Southern Utah 67-66 on Saturday. The Jaguars trailed 66-63 before David Barlow made a layup with 15 seconds left to pull them within one. A Southern Utah turnover and foul set up Cameron's game-winning free throws. IUPUI (8-6, 3-0 Mid-Con) led 33-23 at the half. Southern Utah shot just under 58 percent in the second half and made 8 of its 11 3-pointers. The Thunderbirds (2-13, 1-2 Mid-Con) took their first lead of the second half with 2:28 left on Rand Janes' 3-pointer. Janes finished with a game-high 21 points and had five assists. He was 6-for-9 from 3-point range. Nate Janes had 13 points, six rebounds and three assists for the Thunderbirds. Henry Uhegwu scored 12. Barlow led the Jaguars with 18 points. George Hill, who injured his knee in the Jaguars' Jan. 4 win over Oakland and was expected to miss at least a week, scored 17 points and played 38 minutes. Cameron finished with 13 points and Brandon Cole scored seven and pulled down eight rebounds.
